Diabetes NSW & ACT can help you deliver diabetes education in your local area.
Community Diabetes is a 3 hour face to face workshop for people who are newly
diagnosed or at risk of type 2 diabetes. During this workshop, participants
will learn about the small lifestyle changes that can lead to big health
improvements and empower them to take action to prevent diabetes or diabetes
Workshop size is for up to 20 participants, including partners, a carer or
support person. The program has been translated into Mandarin, Cantonese and
Arabic. Talk to us about other languages you may need.
If you have any questions please call Mina Wanis on 1300 727 194 or email us
Our trained Health Care Professionals: Credentialed Diabetes Educators,
Accredited Practising Dietitians or Accredited Exercise Physiologists will
facilitate the program and you handle the logistics.
Outsource the entire program delivery to us, and free your team from the
administration of program logistics which are time consuming but essential to
the successful delivery of a workshop. At Diabetes NSW & ACT we are highly
